Class ColumnExp<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samskivert.depot.expression.FluentExp<T>
      • com.samskivert.depot.expression.ColumnExp<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SQLExpression<T>, SQLFragment

    public class ColumnExp<T>
extends FluentExp<T>
    An expression that unambiguously identifies a field of a class, for example GameRecord.itemId.

      • as

        public ColumnExp<T> as(Class<? extends PersistentRecord> oClass)
        Returns a column expression for the supplied persistent class with the same name as this expression. This is useful for "casting" a column expression from a parent class to a derived class.

      • addClasses

        public void addClasses(Collection<Class<? extends PersistentRecord>> classSet)
        Description copied from interface: SQLFragment
        Adds all persistent classes that are brought into the SQL context by this clause: FROM clauses, JOINs, UPDATEs, anything that could create a new table abbreviation. This method should recurse into any subordinate state that may in turn bring in new classes so that sub-queries work correctly.
